title: Global Privacy Policy (Mock)
content:
# Global Privacy Policy (Mock)

**Purpose:** Describe how personal data is collected, processed, retained, and protected.

title: Data Retention
content:
## Data Retention
- **Retention Principles:** Personal data is retained only as long as necessary to meet legal, contractual, and business requirements.
- **Retention Schedules:** Retention periods are defined by data category and reviewed periodically.
- **Deletion:** Data deletion is performed using approved processes and is logged when applicable.

title: GDPR Compliance
content:
## GDPR Compliance
- **Lawful Basis:** Processing is performed under a lawful basis (e.g., contract, legitimate interest, consent) as appropriate.
- **Data Subject Rights:** The organization supports access, correction, deletion, portability, and objection requests.
- **Security Measures:** Technical and organizational measures are implemented to protect personal data (encryption, access control, monitoring).

title: Notes for Security Questionnaires
content:
## Notes for Security Questionnaires
This mock covers standard privacy topics requested during vendor due diligence:
- retention schedules
- GDPR alignment
- data subject rights and security controls

title: ISO 27001 Information Security Policy (Mock)
content:
# ISO 27001 Information Security Policy (Mock)

**Purpose:** Define the organizations high-level information security policy and responsibilities.

title: Information Security Roles
content:
## Information Security Roles
- **Information Security Owner:** Accountable for the information security management system (ISMS) and policy compliance.
- **GRC / Compliance Lead:** Maintains security documentation, coordinates audits, and ensures controls are measured and evidenced.
- **System Owners:** Ensure systems are configured securely, monitored, and maintained.
- **All Personnel:** Must follow security policies, report suspected incidents, and complete security awareness training.

title: Asset Management
content:
## Asset Management
- **Asset Inventory:** Critical assets are identified and maintained in an inventory including data classification and ownership.
- **Data Classification:** Data is classified (e.g., Public, Internal, Confidential, Restricted) and handled according to requirements.
- **Acceptable Use:** Assets (devices, accounts, systems) must be used for authorized business purposes.
- **Access Control:** Access is provisioned based on least privilege and reviewed periodically.

title: Control Statements (Questionnaire-Friendly)
content:
## Control Statements (Questionnaire-Friendly)
- The organization maintains documented roles and responsibilities for information security.
- The organization maintains an asset inventory with ownership and classification.
- Access is granted on least privilege and reviewed on a periodic basis.

title: SOC 2 Type II Report (Mock)  v2
content:
# SOC 2 Type II Report (Mock)  v2

**Scope:** This is a realistic mock artifact representing common SOC 2 Type II report content. It is not a real audit report.

title: Logical Access
content:
## Logical Access
- **User Provisioning:** Access is granted based on role and least privilege. Requests require manager approval and are tracked in a ticketing system.
- **Joiner/Mover/Leaver (JML):** Accounts are created, modified, and deactivated according to documented procedures. Deprovisioning occurs within defined SLAs.
- **Privileged Access:** Administrative access is restricted to authorized personnel and reviewed periodically.
- **Access Reviews:** Periodic access reviews are performed for privileged roles and key systems.

title: Encryption at Rest
content:
## Encryption at Rest
- **Standard:** Data stored in production systems is encrypted at rest using industry-standard encryption.
- **Key Management:** Encryption keys are managed through a centralized KMS with access controls and audit logging.
- **Backups:** Backups inherit encryption-at-rest protections and are stored in secured locations.

title: MFA Requirements
content:
## MFA Requirements
- **Enforcement:** MFA is required for administrator access and remote access to production systems.
- **Methods:** Supported methods include authenticator applications and security keys.
- **Exceptions:** Any exception requires documented approval and is time-bound.

title: Notes for Reviewers
content:
## Notes for Reviewers
This mock includes the specific topics commonly requested in vendor security questionnaires:
- logical access controls
- encryption-at-rest controls
- MFA enforcement
